<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Articles</td><form method='post' action=''><input type="hidden" name="PHPSESSID" value="...328fedb22570524062aeb1303" /><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Articles</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/starwarsccg/articles/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/vs/articles/index.php3'>Marvel VS</option><option value='/heroclix/articles/articles.php'>HeroClix</option><option value='/lotr/articles/articles.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/articles/articles.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/articles/articles.php'>Ophidian 2350</option><option value='/magic/treports/treports.php'>The Wastelands</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> LOTR Players Freshness Style Guide<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(3.76)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=12175'>Tim "Fael" Ruesink</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=12175&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> March 24, 2003</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> Lord of the Rings Players Freshness Style Guide<br />
<br />
<br />
--------Warning: this is not a strategy article! Do not rate it for not being so please! This is an article about freshness. Being fresh certainly gives you an advantage at gaming events however so it might just affect your playing skills in the end as well!--------Thanx!<br />
<br />
This an article that might become a little controversial, but just as well it might appeal to many people without rasing an eyebrow. I will give you guys some hints and tips for losing nerd-status in non-gaming life as well as the ability to appear fresh, sharp and fashionable on the gaming scene. A new world might be falling down upon you. Looking good and clean will give you a new status, and you will be trendsetting for other gamers that are still in the smelly caves of nerdness. There is nothing wrong being a gamer, but at least we can all try to look like normal, cool people, right? Gamers have the mental superiority, so why not the looks? Maybe because they never made time for it and just missed some of the crucial key-points. It is these points I would like to cover in this article. BTW:  By saying &#39;you&#39; I don&#39;t mean ALL the Decktech members, but there are always some that fit the definition. If you are already fresh; just read, smile and nod. Have fun!<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
HOW DO WE DO THIS?<br />
<br />
<br />
-Shaving<br />
First of all: you don&#39;t need to shave every day. This varies for everybody, depending on the speed your facial hair grows and of course age. I personaly like to shave once every two (or sometimes 3) days. In summertimes, when the weather is hot, you might want to attend more often to the matter as a shaven face contributes to a sunny and fresh appearance. Use good material for shaving. There are two ways for this: wet shaving and electric. You could use Gillette Mach 3 for wet shaving or one of the newer Philishaves if you prefer electrical shaving. I will cover wet shaving in this article. First of all you want to soften the beardhairs as much as you can. This can be done be pushing a hot towel on your face or simply by splashing some hot water on the areas you plan to shave (I think that should be all of your facial hair, except for your eyebrows. So called &#39;talking vagina&#39;s&#39; are out of fashion here). After this you gently put the shaving cream on your face and neck. Use shaving foam, not gel, because it is less agressive for your skin. Let the cream rest for a minute, you might want to do your hair in the meantime. This gives time for the beardhairs to soften and relax. Now pick your rasor and start the buiseness. I always start shaving in my neck up to my ears and then to the cheeks. This way you leave your chin for the last: the hairs are thick and rough in that part. Try shaving along the way your hairs grow. If you don&#39;t, you might suffer from red aching lines. There are rasors on the market now that allow (Gillette Mach 3 Turbo) you to shave both ways, btw. During shaving hold (clean) your rasor a couple of times under hot water. Hot water, because it makes the blades go  over the skin swifter. Afterwards you splash of all the remaining cream with cold water (cold to ease the skin and prevent it from further dehydration). Use a aftershave with little or no alcohol. The best is aftershave balsam; it moisturises the skin as well as cooling it, making it look healthy.<br />
 <br />
<br />
-Hairdo and Skin (being clean)<br />
Of course you can shave before or after you shower. I advise not to do it while showering, as you will need a clear mirror. For showering of course there is not so much to be said. Do it at least once a day, preferably during the morning, as it wakes you up. Use a vitalising showergel to feel, look and smell fresh. Showering before a tournament is vital. Wash your hair about every two or three days, depending on the use of gel. Best to use a shampoo with a cremeflush: this results in shining and soft hair. Dry your hair carefully and make sure you don&#39;t use a hairdryer (too often). For myself  use the towel after I step from the shower briefly and than I let it dry at roomtemperature for at least 20 minutes. Using gel after that is very much up to your own liking and the tickness of your hair. I use a remix gel that looks like soft chewing gum when you put it in your hands, but works perfectly when applied to my hair. For your haircut I have only one thing to say for the moment: at this very time -short- is the key-word. The shorter the better. Think: Lance Amstrong and some others. &quot;You know of whom I speak&quot;. Spikes are all right as long as they are kept short and to a &#39;purpose&#39;, random spikes are to freaky right now. The same goes for sidewhiskers in an even greater extend: LOTR-players tend to have way too long whiskers. Keep&#39;m short and tidy or have them long but pointy. Big long broad whiskers are out. -period-<br />
<br />
<br />
-Fingernails<br />
Cut your fingernails once a week, don&#39;t bite &#39;m. Make sure you don&#39;t put them in your nose to often as it leaves those black trails under the nails.<br />
<br />
<br />
-Teeth and mouth<br />
So, there it is. The point where all girls will stand or fall. You might look the most handsome guy on the planet, but if you open your mouth and she sees rotten brown teeth she&#39;s a goner. This well known white/yellow stuff near your toothflesh can be enough to leave her disgusted. Brush your teeth AT LEAST twice a day, if not thrice. Now here comes an interesting fact: If you just finished your breakfast it is unwise to immediately brush your teeth before you go of to your tourney. Why you ask? Well, as you eat some ingredients turn into an acid when they mix in with your slime. The acid attacks the ivory on your teeth. It is completely natural and nothing to be worried of as your mouthal flora will restore to a normal PH-level within 40 minutes. BUT: in these 40 mintes your tooth-ivory will be temporarily weakened. By brushing it you might actually brush some ivory away; not much, but still if you do it time and time again you will be more vulnarable to carries (holes). Soooo, you should brush your teeth before breakfast, to strenghten them. After breakfast flush you mouth with (mouth)water and maybe take an (dental) chewinggum with natural whitener. This way you keep your breath fresh, and your teeth strong and white. Also do not buy cheap-ass toothpaste: mouth and teeth are very important to humans; treat them with the materials they deserve!<br />
<br />
<br />
-Food<br />
This is dangerous to talk about as food is soo region-bound. Just try to eat lot&#39;s of fruit, and not so much of fries. Drink a lot of water, at least 6 liters a day. It keeps your skin moisturised, your breath pleasant, and your digestion in good &#39;shape&#39;. Don&#39;t eat smelly things like onions or garlic the night before a tournament. The smell of it will not only find it&#39;s way out your mouth but also through your skin, your sweat. After eating fat, it happens, don&#39;t touch your face with greased fingers! During a tournament make sure you bring sufficient food and drinks. An emergency pack of serials and some packs with fruit juice or water are always a good thing to bring. By eating healthy stuff you will feel fit and sharp. You will be more focused in important games that way.<br />
<br />
<br />
-Smell<br />
This is not only handled by deodorant, but deo is a good thing for some gamers to start with. It all starts with the morning shower. After toweling apply deo to your armpits and a little to some other parts of your body. AXE is good stuff. Don&#39;t overdo it however. There are some stories of kids who died after spraying themselves under deo: their body could longer sweat sufficient so they died of overheating! Bring your deo to your tourney and refresh maybe two times during the day, depending on the atmosphere of where you are playing. Don&#39;t do it in public however! The sight of your opponent deoring before the round starts is somewhat yuk. You might want to use aftershave or &#39;eau the toilet&#39; for more subtle sents; if there are some nice girls around for instance. The stuff is expensive but rewarding. Use a subtle sent, not too overwhelming and use it only once a day. After some 30 minutes after applying it you can&#39;t smell the sent yourself anymore, but that doesn&#39;t mean it&#39;s gone! It is still there, but your brains don&#39;r register it anymore, that&#39;s all. Use &#39;eau&#39;s and aftershaves with little acohol and apply them to your chest, not the face. Smells go upwards so there is no need to put it on your neck or face where it would dehydrate the skin. What I use: Platinum Egoist by Chanel Paris (this is an eau d&#39; toilet that cost about 50 dollars but will last you for some months!)<br />
<br />
<br />
-Body language<br />
Be relaxed, but sharp. Look interested in others and smile when you want too. Keep your chest up front and always look up high, instead of to the floor. Think free, so you look intruiging but open. I cannot tell you how to do that, just try.<br />
<br />
<br />
-Clothing and shoes<br />
Look on the streets and into shops, what are fashion retailers wearing themselves? You don&#39;t need to buy expensive brands, it is just about the way it looks, but sometimes it can be rewarding to buy something retardedly expensive. The golden rule is that if you like something and think it would be fashionable for YOU to wear, than you HAVE to buy it. If it really gets too expensive you might want to wait for the price to drop; you just might be lucky if you visit the same shop again two weeks later. If you really want to go into brands, here are some. (But again; you don&#39;t need to buy these brands for just their name and tag, you might as well find something almost the same for halve the money). DKNY, D&G, Diesel, Hugo Boss are some of the brands that go very well right now. For shoes, if you want sneakers/ gymps, you might want to go for Puma. (they have some good jackets and shirts as well).<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
Hope you learned AND / OR enjoyed. You may have wasted some minutes of your time by reading this, but just as well this might save you a couple of years! <br></font><BR><font class="bfont"> <A HREF='/lotr/articles/articles.php?id=4589&view=1&PHPSESSID=...328fedb22570524062aeb1303'>Read the Reviews</a><font class="bfont"> | <A HREF='/lotr/articles/articles.php?PHPSESSID=...328fedb22570524062aeb1303'>Back to List</A></font><p><font class="bfont"> <b>You must be a member to contribute to Decktech.</b>  <p>Please <a href='/lotr/main/join.php?PHPSESSID=...328fedb22570524062aeb1303'> become a registered member</a></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
